en_862337_0	Colombo (News 1st): The Department of Railways says that the schedule of the Northern Railway Line has been changed from today (August 1).
en_862337_1	In a statement, the department said the timetables have been changed taking into consideration the new trends in passenger needs.
en_862337_2	According to the Department of Railways, the morning and night trains from Talaimannar to Colombo Fort via Anuradhapura, Medawachchiya will now operate from Colombo Fort to Kankesanthurai via Talaimannar and Jaffna.
en_862337_3	A survey done by the Railway Department reveals that the number of passengers travelling from Talaimannar to Anuradhapura via Medawachchiya and Colombo Fort has decreased and the number of passengers travelling from Fort to Jaffna and Kankesanthurai have increased.
